doc.after: Quaggas have been reported gathering into herds of 30â50 individuals and sometimes travelled in a linear fashion.[12] They may have been sympatric with Burchell's zebra between the Vaal and Orange rivers.[8][26] This is disputed,[8] and there is no evidence that they interbred.[26] It could also have shared a small portion of its range with Hartmann's mountain zebra (Equus zebra hartmannae).[19]
